  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    The system integration artifact will be tested against the system design specification, technical and functional safety&#xD;
    requirements to ensure compliance against those documents.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Tests used to verify the hardware and software implementation should also be completed.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The tests are intended to provide evidence that each element of the system interacts correctly and complies with the&#xD;
    technical and functional safety concepts, and to give an adequate level of confidence that unintended behaviors, that&#xD;
    could violate a safety goal, are absent&#xD;
&lt;/p>&lt;br /></mainDescription>
  <purpose>To test the systems integration against the system design specification, technical and functional safety requirements&#xD;
according to the Systems integration verification (test) plan and test specification.</purpose>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription>
